.SH NAME
drm_atomic_helper_bridge_destroy_state \- Destroy a bridge state object
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_atomic_helper_bridge_destroy_state
.BI "(struct drm_bridge *bridge "  ","
.BI "struct drm_bridge_state *state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bridge" 12
the bridge this state refers to
.IP "state" 12
bridge state to destroy
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Destroys a bridge state previously created by
&\fBdrm_atomic_helper_bridge_reset\fP or
&\fBdrm_atomic_helper_bridge_duplicate_state\fP. This helper is meant to be
used as a bridge \fIdrm_bridge_funcs.atomic_destroy_state\fP hook for bridges
that don't subclass the bridge state.
